# $Id: README,v 8.0 1996/03/13 15:35:02 kb207252 Dist $

Purge is run my cron at night to remove unwanted (aged) backup files
from the system OLD dirs.

Here is a suggested crontab line:
	0 2 * * 1	purge -v -unews -uuucp / >>/usr/adm/purge.log 2>/tmp/prg$$; [ -s /tmp/prg$$ ] && Mail -s "purge failed" root </tmp/prg$$

kayessbee
